  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs
      (NSAIDs) were associated with acute kidney injury (AKI) in patients with heart failure. In
      addition, the investigators would like to assess the risk of admission for acute
      decompensated heart failure following exposure to NSAIDs within 30 days.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
